Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getIlmType(25.10)                                            getIlmType(25.10)

Name
       getIlmType - Displays information about the specified setIlmType in the
       Innovus log file and the Innovus console

Syntax
       getIlmType

       [-help]

       [-model]

       Displays  information about the specified setIlmType in the Innovus log
       file and the Innovus console. Displays the following information:

              * Parameter name

              * Current value

              * Type (boolean, string, and so on)

              * The current value set by the user

       If you do not specify a parameter, the Innovus software displays infor-
       mation for all of the setIlmType parameters.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each getIlmType parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man getIlmType

       -model Outputs the model.

Examples
              * The  following  example  displays  the current setting for the
                -model parameter:

                getIlmType -model

                The software displays the following information:

                timing

Related Information
              * setIlmType

